"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/676048","Department of Health","false","2017-01-30","<p>The Department does not provide specific guidance on the use of paediatric speech and language therapy, paediatric physiotherapy and paediatric occupational therapy for children and young people with cerebral palsy.</p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline on the management of spasticity in under 19s includes recommendations on the provision of physiotherapy and/or occupational therapy.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, at the request of the Department, NICE published, on 25 January 2017, the clinical guideline Cerebral palsy in under 25s: assessment and management.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-01-30T16:05:14.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/676048/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/676048/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/676048/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-01-20","Cerebral Palsy: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what guidance his Department provides on the use of (a) paediatric speech and language therapy, (b) paediatric physiotherapy and (c) paediatric occupational therapy for children and young people with cerebral palsy.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","61046"
